  "prompt": "What is the best drama (genre) movie?",
  "response": "The \"best\" drama movie can be subjective as it depends on individual preferences. However, one highly acclaimed drama film that is often considered among the best is:\n\n**\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)**\n- **Director:** Frank Darabont\n- **Starring:** Tim Robbins, Morgan Freeman\n- **Plot:** The story follows the life of banker Andy Dufresne, who is wrongfully convicted of murder and sent to Shawshank Prison. Over the years, he builds an unlikely friendship with fellow inmate Ellis \"Red\" Redding and works to improve the prison conditions while maintaining hope and determination to prove his innocence.\n\nThis film is celebrated for its powerful performances, compelling narrative, and themes of hope, perseverance, and friendship. It has received widespread critical acclaim and is a favorite among many movie enthusiasts.\n\nOther notable mentions in the drama genre that are highly regarded include:\n- **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)**\n- **\"The Godfather\" (1972)**\n- **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)**\n- **\"12 Years a Slave\" (2013)**\n\nIf you have specific preferences or themes you enjoy, I can recommend more tailored suggestions!",
